-- UniCredit May Appoint Deputy CEO Nicastro General Manager, Corriere Says
-- B y   A r m o r e l   K e n n a
-- 2010-09-25T09:13:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-25/unicredit-may-appoint-deputy-ceo-nicastro-general-manager-corriere-says.html
UniCredit SpA , Italy’s largest
bank, may appoint  Roberto Nicastro , one of four deputy chief
executive officers, to a new position of general manager, daily
Corriere della Sera reported, without saying where it got the
information.  The introduction of the general manager position at the
bank would satisfy UniCredit’s banking foundation  investors ,
Corriere reported. Nicastro also may be considered for the CEO
job, following the resignation of Alessandro Profumo, the
newspaper said. UniCredit declined to comment on the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Armorel Kenna  in Milan at 
 akenna@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net  